The bodies of the two missing eThekwini municipal workers have been found.  JOHANNESBURG - The bodies of the two missing eThekwini municipal workers have been found. Solomon Shandu and Simphiwe Cele's bodies were recovered from the Umdloti River a considerable distance from where their car was retrieved. The pair disappeared on Saturday after returning from a funeral. Their car was swept away while crossing a makeshift bridge during floods in the region. eThekwini Mayor, Mxolisi Kaunda, has thanked the search and rescue teams for not giving up on the search.